This paper focuses on robotic manipulation, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The method involves using visual observations to learn pushing and grasping actions, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) is also relevant. The use of deep reinforcement learning (DRL) for learning these actions suggests machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) are also relevant subfields. Finally, the paper also discusses the generalization of the method to novel objects, which suggests systems and control (cs.SY) may also be relevant.
